 <section xml:id="introduction-quickstart-scc">
  <title>Introduction</title>
   <para>
    &productname; is a technology and support solution for mixed Linux environments.
    With a &productname; subscription, you can register and update &rhel; and CentOS Linux from repositories provided by &suse;. Optional &ha; repositories are also available.
   </para>
   <important role="compact">
    <para>
     CentOS&nbsp;Stream is not supported.
    </para>
   </important>
   <para>
    This guide describes how to register directly with the &scc;. <emphasis role="bold">This
    registration method is only available for CentOS&nbsp;Linux&nbsp;&productnumber; with the
    <emphasis>&productname; Lite</emphasis> subscription.</emphasis> To register &rhel; or
    CentOS&nbsp;Linux with a different &productname; subscription, you must use &smlm; or &rmt;.
   </para>
   <orderedlist>
    <title>Procedure overview</title>
    <listitem>
     <para>
       <xref linkend="find-registration-code"/>. You must have a valid registration code to register
       your system to the &scc;.
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
       <xref linkend="register-with-scc"/>. &suse; provides a registration script to simplify the
       process of adding &suse; repositories to a non-&suse; system.
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </orderedlist>

